acl.name: acl
acl.description: The MIB module for the Access Control List configuration and statistics.

aclCurCfgTable.name: aclCurCfgTable
aclCurCfgTable.description: The table of current ACL configuration.

aclCurCfgEntry.name: aclCurCfgEntry
aclCurCfgEntry.description: Current information about a particular ACL configuration entry.

aclCurCfgIndex.name: aclCurCfgIndex
aclCurCfgIndex.description: The index associated with this ACL entry.

aclCurCfgBlock.name: aclCurCfgBlock
aclCurCfgBlock.description: The index of the ACL block to which this ACL entry is a member of. A value of zero means the ACL is not a member of any block.

aclCurCfgGroup.name: aclCurCfgGroup
aclCurCfgGroup.description: The index of the ACL group to which this ACL entry is a member of. A value of zero means the ACL is not a member of any group.

aclCurCfgFilterAction.name: aclCurCfgFilterAction
aclCurCfgFilterAction.description: The action to be performed on a packet that matches the filter settings of this ACL entry.

aclCurCfgFilterActionSetCOS.name: aclCurCfgFilterActionSetCOS
aclCurCfgFilterActionSetCOS.description: The value to be used when the action to be performed is setCOS for this ACL entry.

aclCurCfgEthFmt.name: aclCurCfgEthFmt
aclCurCfgEthFmt.description: The packet ethernet format to be filtered.

aclCurCfgTagFmt.name: aclCurCfgTagFmt
aclCurCfgTagFmt.description: The packet tag format to be filtered.

aclCurCfgSrcMACAddress.name: aclCurCfgSrcMACAddress
aclCurCfgSrcMACAddress.description: The source MAC address to be filtered.

aclCurCfgSrcMACMask.name: aclCurCfgSrcMACMask
aclCurCfgSrcMACMask.description: The address mask applied to aclCurCfgSrcMACAddress for filtering.

aclCurCfgDstMACAddress.name: aclCurCfgDstMACAddress
aclCurCfgDstMACAddress.description: The destination MAC address to be filtered.

aclCurCfgDstMACMask.name: aclCurCfgDstMACMask
aclCurCfgDstMACMask.description: The address mask applied to aclCurCfgDstMACAddress for filtering.

aclCurCfgEthernetTypeName.name: aclCurCfgEthernetTypeName
aclCurCfgEthernetTypeName.description: The Ethernet type to be filtered. If the value of this object is other(7), the value of aclNewCfgEthernetTypeValue indicates the ethernet type that will be filtered.

aclCurCfgEthernetTypeValue.name: aclCurCfgEthernetTypeValue
aclCurCfgEthernetTypeValue.description: The Ethernet type value to be filtered. The value of this object is equivalent to the value of aclNewCfgEthernetTypeName except when the value of aclNewCfgEthernetTypeName is other(7), which can be any user-defined value for this object.

aclCurCfgVLanId.name: aclCurCfgVLanId
aclCurCfgVLanId.description: The virtual LAN identifier to be filtered.

aclCurCfgVLanMask.name: aclCurCfgVLanMask
aclCurCfgVLanMask.description: The mask applied to aclCurCfgVLanId for filtering.

aclCurCfgTypeOfService.name: aclCurCfgTypeOfService
aclCurCfgTypeOfService.description: The type of service to be filtered.

aclCurCfgSrcIPAddress.name: aclCurCfgSrcIPAddress
aclCurCfgSrcIPAddress.description: The source IP address to be filtered.

aclCurCfgSrcIPMask.name: aclCurCfgSrcIPMask
aclCurCfgSrcIPMask.description: The address mask applied to aclCurCfgSrcIPAddress for filtering.

aclCurCfgDstIPAddress.name: aclCurCfgDstIPAddress
aclCurCfgDstIPAddress.description: The destination IP address to be filtered.

aclCurCfgDstIPMask.name: aclCurCfgDstIPMask
aclCurCfgDstIPMask.description: The address mask applied to aclCurCfgDstIPAddress for filtering.

aclCurCfgSrcPort.name: aclCurCfgSrcPort
aclCurCfgSrcPort.description: The source TCP/UDP port number to be filtered.

aclCurCfgSrcPortMask.name: aclCurCfgSrcPortMask
aclCurCfgSrcPortMask.description: The mask applied to aclCurCfgSrcPort for filtering.

aclCurCfgDstPort.name: aclCurCfgDstPort
aclCurCfgDstPort.description: The destination TCP/UDP port number to be filtered.

aclCurCfgDstPortMask.name: aclCurCfgDstPortMask
aclCurCfgDstPortMask.description: The mask applied to aclCurCfgDstPort for filtering.

aclCurCfgTCPFlags.name: aclCurCfgTCPFlags
aclCurCfgTCPFlags.description: The TCP flags to be filtered. OCTET xxxxxxxx ||||..|| ||||..||_tcpFIN(7) ||||..|__tcpSYN(6) |||| ||||_____tcpACK(3) |||______tcpURG(2) ||_______reserved2(1) |________reserved1(0) where: - reserved1 - 0; - reserved2 - 0; - x - 0 or 1;

aclCurCfgTCPFlagsMask.name: aclCurCfgTCPFlagsMask
aclCurCfgTCPFlagsMask.description: The TCP flags mask. OCTET xxxxxxxx ||||..|| ||||..||_tcpFIN(7) ||||..|__tcpSYN(6) |||| ||||_____tcpACK(3) |||______tcpURG(2) ||_______reserved2(1) |________reserved1(0) where: - reserved1 - 0; - reserved2 - 0; - x - 0 or 1;

aclCurCfgEgressPorts.name: aclCurCfgEgressPorts
aclCurCfgEgressPorts.description: The port list in the ACL configured for egress filtering. The ports are presented in bitmap format, as follows: OCTET 1 OCTET 2 ..... xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx ..... || || | || || |_ port 9 || || || ||___ port 8 || |____ port 7 || . . . ||_________ port 2 |__________ port 1 where x: 1 - the represented port is configured for filtering. 0 - the represented port is not configured for filtering.

aclCurCfgStatistics.name: aclCurCfgStatistics
aclCurCfgStatistics.description: Whether statistics collection for this ACL is enabled or not.

aclNewCfgTable.name: aclNewCfgTable
aclNewCfgTable.description: The table of new ACL configuration.

aclNewCfgEntry.name: aclNewCfgEntry
aclNewCfgEntry.description: New information about a particular ACL configuration.

aclNewCfgIndex.name: aclNewCfgIndex
aclNewCfgIndex.description: The index associated with this ACL entry.

aclNewCfgBlock.name: aclNewCfgBlock
aclNewCfgBlock.description: The index of the ACL block to which this ACL entry is a member of. A value of zero means the ACL is not a member of any block.

aclNewCfgGroup.name: aclNewCfgGroup
aclNewCfgGroup.description: The index of the ACL group to which this ACL entry is a member of. A value of zero means the ACL is not a member of any group.

aclNewCfgFilterAction.name: aclNewCfgFilterAction
aclNewCfgFilterAction.description: The action to be performed on a packet that matches the filter settings of this ACL entry.

aclNewCfgFilterActionSetCOS.name: aclNewCfgFilterActionSetCOS
aclNewCfgFilterActionSetCOS.description: The COS queue to be used when the action for this ACL entry is set to SetCOS.

aclNewCfgEthFmt.name: aclNewCfgEthFmt
aclNewCfgEthFmt.description: The packet ethernet format to be filtered.

aclNewCfgTagFmt.name: aclNewCfgTagFmt
aclNewCfgTagFmt.description: The packet tagging format to be filtered.

aclNewCfgSrcMACAddress.name: aclNewCfgSrcMACAddress
aclNewCfgSrcMACAddress.description: The source MAC address to be filtered. Whenever this object is set to a nonzero value, the aclNewCfgSrcMACMask object, if not yet set, will be automatically set to ff:ff:ff:ff:ff.

aclNewCfgSrcMACMask.name: aclNewCfgSrcMACMask
aclNewCfgSrcMACMask.description: The address mask to be applied to aclNewCfgSrcMACAddress for filtering.

aclNewCfgDstMACAddress.name: aclNewCfgDstMACAddress
aclNewCfgDstMACAddress.description: The destination MAC address to be filtered. Whenever this object is set to a nonzero value, the aclNewCfgDstMACMask object, if not yet set, will be automatically set to ff:ff:ff:ff:ff.

aclNewCfgDstMACMask.name: aclNewCfgDstMACMask
aclNewCfgDstMACMask.description: The address mask to be applied to aclNewCfgDstMACAddress for filtering.

aclNewCfgEthernetTypeName.name: aclNewCfgEthernetTypeName
aclNewCfgEthernetTypeName.description: The Ethernet type to be filtered. If the value of this object is other(7), the value of aclNewCfgEthernetTypeValue indicates the ethernet type that will be filtered. If this object is set to a value other than other(7), the value of the aclNewCfgEthernetTypeValue object is automatically set, as follows: aclNewCfgEthernetTypeName aclNewCfgEthernetTypeValue none(0) 0 arp(1) 2054 (0x0806) ipv4(2) 2048 (0x0800) ipv6(3) 34525 (0x86dd) mpls(4) 34887 (0x8847) rarp(5) 32821 (0x8035) any(6) 65535 (0xffff)

aclNewCfgEthernetTypeValue.name: aclNewCfgEthernetTypeValue
aclNewCfgEthernetTypeValue.description: The Ethernet type value to be filtered. The value of this object is equivalent to the value of aclNewCfgEthernetTypeName except when the value of aclNewCfgEthernetTypeName is other(7), which can be any user-defined value for this object.

aclNewCfgVLanId.name: aclNewCfgVLanId
aclNewCfgVLanId.description: The virtual LAN identifier to be filtered. Whenever this object is set to a nonzero value, the aclNewCfgVLanMask object, if not yet set, will be automatically set to 4095 (0xfff).

aclNewCfgVLanMask.name: aclNewCfgVLanMask
aclNewCfgVLanMask.description: The mask to be applied to aclNewCfgVLanId for filtering.

aclNewCfgTypeOfService.name: aclNewCfgTypeOfService
aclNewCfgTypeOfService.description: The type of service to be filtered.

aclNewCfgSrcIPAddress.name: aclNewCfgSrcIPAddress
aclNewCfgSrcIPAddress.description: The source IP address to be filtered. Whenever this object is set to a nonzero value, the aclNewCfgSrcIPMask object, if not yet set, will be automatically set to 255.255.255.255.

aclNewCfgSrcIPMask.name: aclNewCfgSrcIPMask
aclNewCfgSrcIPMask.description: The address mask to be applied to aclNewCfgSrcIPAddress for filtering.

aclNewCfgDstIPAddress.name: aclNewCfgDstIPAddress
aclNewCfgDstIPAddress.description: The destination IP address to be filtered. Whenever this object is set to a nonzero value, the aclNewCfgDstIPMask object, if not yet set, will be automatically set to 255.255.255.255.

aclNewCfgDstIPMask.name: aclNewCfgDstIPMask
aclNewCfgDstIPMask.description: The address mask to be applied to aclNewCfgDstIPAddress for filtering.

aclNewCfgSrcPort.name: aclNewCfgSrcPort
aclNewCfgSrcPort.description: The source TCP/UDP port number to be filtered. Whenever this object is set if the aclNewCfgSrcPortMask object is not set will be automatically set to 65535 (0xffff).

aclNewCfgSrcPortMask.name: aclNewCfgSrcPortMask
aclNewCfgSrcPortMask.description: The mask to be applied to aclNewCfgSrcPort for filtering.

aclNewCfgDstPort.name: aclNewCfgDstPort
aclNewCfgDstPort.description: The destination TCP/UDP port number to be filtered. Whenever this object is set the aclNewCfgSrcPortMask object, if not yet set, will be automatically set to 65535 (0xffff).

aclNewCfgDstPortMask.name: aclNewCfgDstPortMask
aclNewCfgDstPortMask.description: The mask to be applied to aclNewCfgDstPort for filtering.

aclNewCfgTCPFlags.name: aclNewCfgTCPFlags
aclNewCfgTCPFlags.description: The TCP flags to be filtered. The TCP flags are presented in bitmap format, as follows: OCTET xxxxxxxx ||||..|| ||||..||_tcpFIN(7) ||||..|__tcpSYN(6) |||| ||||_____tcpACK(3) |||______tcpURG(2) ||_______reserved2(1) |________reserved1(0) where: - reserved1 - 0; - reserved2 - 0; - x - 0 or 1;

aclNewCfgTCPFlagsMask.name: aclNewCfgTCPFlagsMask
aclNewCfgTCPFlagsMask.description: The TCP flags mask. The TCP flags are presented in bitmap format, as follows: OCTET xxxxxxxx ||||..|| ||||..||_tcpFIN(7) ||||..|__tcpSYN(6) |||| ||||_____tcpACK(3) |||______tcpURG(2) ||_______reserved2(1) |________reserved1(0) where: - reserved1 - 0; - reserved2 - 0; - x - 0 or 1; Default value is 0x3f.

aclNewCfgEgressPorts.name: aclNewCfgEgressPorts
aclNewCfgEgressPorts.description: The port list in the ACL configured for egress filtering. The ports are presented in bitmap format, as follows: OCTET 1 OCTET 2 ..... xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx ..... || || | || || |_ port 9 || || || ||___ port 8 || |____ port 7 || . . . ||_________ port 2 |__________ port 1 where x: 1 - the represented port is configured for filtering. 0 - the represented port is not configured for filtering.

aclNewCfgStatistics.name: aclNewCfgStatistics
aclNewCfgStatistics.description: Whether statistics collection for this ACL is enabled or not.

aclNewCfgAddEgressPort.name: aclNewCfgAddEgressPort
aclNewCfgAddEgressPort.description: The port to be added to the specified ACL for egress filtering. A value of zero is always returned when this object is read.

aclNewCfgRemoveEgressPort.name: aclNewCfgRemoveEgressPort
aclNewCfgRemoveEgressPort.description: The port to be removed from the specified ACL. A value of zero is always returned when this object is read.

aclNewCfgDelete.name: aclNewCfgDelete
aclNewCfgDelete.description: This is an action object to delete an ACL entry. A value of other(1) is always returned when this object is read.

aclBlockCurCfgTable.name: aclBlockCurCfgTable
aclBlockCurCfgTable.description: The table of current ACL block configuration.

aclBlockCurCfgEntry.name: aclBlockCurCfgEntry
aclBlockCurCfgEntry.description: Current information about a particular ACL block configuration.

aclBlockCurCfgIndex.name: aclBlockCurCfgIndex
aclBlockCurCfgIndex.description: The index associated with this ACL block entry.

aclBlockCurCfgMemberAcls.name: aclBlockCurCfgMemberAcls
aclBlockCurCfgMemberAcls.description: The ACL members of this ACL block, presented in bitmap format, as follows: OCTET 1 OCTET 2 ..... xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx ..... || || | || || |_ ACL 9 || || || ||___ ACL 8 || |____ ACL 7 || . . . ||_________ ACL 2 |__________ ACL 1 where x: 1 - the represented ACL is a member of the block. 0 - the represented ACL is not a member of the block.

aclBlockNewCfgTable.name: aclBlockNewCfgTable
aclBlockNewCfgTable.description: The table of new ACL block configuration.

aclBlockNewCfgEntry.name: aclBlockNewCfgEntry
aclBlockNewCfgEntry.description: New information about a particular ACL block configuration.

aclBlockNewCfgIndex.name: aclBlockNewCfgIndex
aclBlockNewCfgIndex.description: The index associated with this ACL block entry.

aclBlockNewCfgMemberAcls.name: aclBlockNewCfgMemberAcls
aclBlockNewCfgMemberAcls.description: The ACL members of this ACL block, presented in bitmap format, as follows: OCTET 1 OCTET 2 ..... xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx ..... || || | || || |_ ACL 9 || || || ||___ ACL 8 || |____ ACL 7 || . . . ||_________ ACL 2 |__________ ACL 1 where x: 1 - the represented ACL is a member of the block. 0 - the represented ACL is not a member of the block.

aclBlockNewCfgAddAcl.name: aclBlockNewCfgAddAcl
aclBlockNewCfgAddAcl.description: The index of the ACL entry to be added into this ACL block. A successful set operation on this object will also set the bit corresponding to the ACL entry in the aclBlockNewCfgMemberAcls bitmap. A value of zero is always returned when this object is read.

aclBlockNewCfgRemoveAcl.name: aclBlockNewCfgRemoveAcl
aclBlockNewCfgRemoveAcl.description: The index of the ACL entry to be removed from this ACL block. A successful set operation on this object will unset the bit corresponding to the ACL entry in the aclBlockNewCfgMemberAcls bitmap. A value of zero is always returned when this object is read.

aclBlockNewCfgDelete.name: aclBlockNewCfgDelete
aclBlockNewCfgDelete.description: This is an action object to delete an ACL block. A value of other(1) is always returned when this object is read.

aclGroupNewCfgMemberBlocks.description: The ACL block members of this ACL group, presented in bitmap format, as follows: OCTET 1 OCTET 2 ..... xxxxxxxx xxxxxxxx ..... || || | || || |_ ACL Block 9 || || || ||___ ACL Block 8 || |____ ACL Block 7 || . . . . ||_________ ACL Block 2 |__________ ACL Block 1 where x: 1 - the represented ACL block is a member of the group. 0 - the represented ACL block is not a member of the group.
